---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const title = "Privacy Policy | CC3PO Docs";
const description = "Privacy Policy for CC3PO documentation and knowledge base.";
---

<Layout title={title}>
  <div class="legal-page">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="last-updated">Last Updated: April 23, 2026</p>
    
    <div class="legal-content">
      <section>
        <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
        <p>When you use CC3PO documentation, we may collect:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> Pages visited, time spent, search queries</li>
          <li><strong>Device Information:</strong> Browser type, device type, screen resolution</li>
          <li><strong>Cookies:</strong> Session cookies for functionality</li>
        </ul>
      </section>
      
      <section>
        <h2>2. How We Use Information</h2>
        <p>We use collected information to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Improve documentation quality and relevance</li>
          <li>Analyze which guides are most helpful</li>
          <li>Fix errors and update outdated content</li>
          <li>Provide technical support when requested</li>
        </ul>
      </section>
      
      <section>
        <h2>3. Cookies and Tracking</h2>
        <p>We use minimal cookies for:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Session Management:</strong> Remembering your preferences</li>
          <li><strong>Analytics:</strong> Understanding how documentation is used (anonymized)</li>
          <li><strong>Functionality:</strong> Search history and navigation</li>
        </ul>
        <p>You can disable cookies in your browser settings. The documentation will remain accessible.</p>
      </section>
      
      <section>
        <h2>4. Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p>We may use the following third-party services:</p>
        <table>
          <tr>
            <th>Service</th>
            <th>Purpose</th>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Netlify</td>
            <td>Hosting and deployment</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Google Analytics</td>
            <td>Usage analytics (if enabled)</td>
          </tr>
        </table>
      </section>
      
      <section>
        <h2>5. Data Retention</h2>
        <p>We retain analytics data for:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Page views: 14 months</li>
          <li>Search queries: 30 days</li>
          <li>Session data: 24 hours</li>
        </ul>
      </section>
      
      <section>
        <h2>6. Your Rights</h2>
        <p>You have the right to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Request a copy of your data</li>
          <li>Request deletion of your data</li>
          <li>Opt-out of analytics tracking</li>
          <li>Disable cookies in your browser</li>
        </ul>
      </section>
      
      <section>
        <h2>7. California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA)</h2>
        <p>California residents have additional rights:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Right to know what personal information is collected</li>
          <li>Right to request deletion</li>
          <li>Right to opt-out of the sale of personal information</li>
          <li>Right to non-discrimination for exercising these rights</li>
        </ul>
        <p><strong>We do not sell personal information.</strong></p>
      </section>
      
      <section>
        <h2>8. Security</h2>
        <p>We implement reasonable security measures:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>HTTPS encryption for all connections</li>
          <li>Minimal data collection (only what's needed)</li>
          <li>No storage of sensitive personal information</li>
        </ul>
      </section>
      
      <section>
        <h2>9. Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p>This documentation is intended for professionals. We do not knowingly collect information from children under 13.</p>
      </section>
      
      <section>
        <h2>10. Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Changes will be posted on this page with an updated "Last Updated" date.</p>
      </section>
      
      <section>
        <h2>11. Contact Information</h2>
        <p>For questions about this Privacy Policy:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Email: <a href="mailto:privacy@cc3po.com">privacy@cc3po.com</a></li>
          <li>Website: <a href="https://cc3po.com/privacy-policy/">cc3po.com/privacy-policy/</a></li>
        </ul>
      </section>
    </div>
    
    <div class="back-link">
      <a href="/">← Back to Knowledge Base</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .legal-page {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 40px 24px;
  }
  
  h1 {
    color: #6b35ff;
    font-size: 32px;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }
  
  .last-updated {
    color: #888;
    font-size: 14px;
    margin-bottom: 40px;
  }
  
  h2 {
    color: #1a1a2e;
    font-size: 20px;
    margin-top: 32px;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }
  
  p, li {
    color: #4a4a5a;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }
  
  ul {
    margin-left: 24px;
    margin-top: 8px;
  }
  
  li {
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }
  
  table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    margin: 16px 0;
  }
  
  th, td {
    padding: 12px;
    text-align: left;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(107, 53, 255, 0.1);
  }
  
  th {
    background: rgba(107, 53, 255, 0.05);
    color: #1a1a2e;
  }
  
  a {
    color: #6b35ff;
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  
  a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }
  
  .back-link {
    margin-top: 48px;
    padding-top: 24px;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(107, 53, 255, 0.1);
  }
</style>